Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["InaccessibleOperatorQ", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844505106193314*^9, 3.844505110275084*^9}, {
   3.8479726623493013`*^9, 3.8479726647483473`*^9}, 3.8479726982678714`*^9, {
   3.892185626129051*^9, 3.8921856285102596`*^9}, {3.892290353328762*^9, 
   3.892290358216865*^9}, 
   3.8925461415089827`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"720df81e-e32b-4e72-a2ae-\
288ae75dc22b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"InaccessibleOperatorQ", "::", "usage"}], " ", "=", " ", 
   "\"\<InaccessibleOperatorQ determines which of a given set of operators \
{\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(1\), \
\(f\)]\),\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(2\), \
\(f\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(n\), \(f\)]\)} is inaccessible \
from an initial operator \!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) under Hamiltonian \
evolution generated by the Hamiltonian algebra {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(1\
\)]\),\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(2\)]\),..., \!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(N\)]\)}.\n\nThe syntax distinguishes two cases:\n\n1) \
InaccessibleOperatorQ[\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) \[Rule] \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(f\)]\), {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}] returns True or False \
depending on whether \!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(f\)]\) is inaccessible from \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) under {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}-evolution.\n\n2) \
InaccessibleOperatorQ[\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) \[Rule] \
{\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(1\), \
\(f\)]\),\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(2\), \
\(f\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(n\), \(f\)]\)}, \
{\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}] \
returns a list of True and False depending on whether the various \
{\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(1\), \
\(f\)]\),\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(2\), \
\(f\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubsuperscriptBox[\(Q\), \(n\), \(f\)]\)} are inaccessible \
from \!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) under {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}-evolution.\n\nAn output of \
True indicates that the desired operator is not accessible from \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) under {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}-evolution. An output of \
False indicates that the operator may or may not be accessible from \
\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(Q\), \(i\)]\) under {\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \
\(1\)]\),...,\!\(\*SubscriptBox[\(H\), \(N\)]\)}-evolution.\n\>\""}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.547025606968602*^9, 3.547025615213552*^9}, {
   3.682594281787702*^9, 3.682594297089982*^9}, 3.7195728001256537`*^9, {
