   3.892269380597375*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"134eae83-15c0-4f75-9734-\
e48e9a9319b4"],

Cell["\<\
03/05/23/CB - 1) LieAlgebra now traps arguments that are not a list of \
operators. 2) The main routine for LieAlgebra has been rewritten to fix \
looping and improve performance. 

04/05/23/CB - 1) Inclusion of MaximalAbelianQ which checks if a given \
subalgebra is abelian. 2) Inclusion of AbelianSubalgebra, which extends a \
given starting algebra to an abelian subalgebra. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6992793268113956`*^9, 3.699279350177552*^9}, {
  3.750413547171677*^9, 3.750413564604564*^9}, {3.89211347520656*^9, 
  3.892113545599037*^9}, {3.892203765897711*^9, 
  3.89220382657847*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ee8e0438-76a0-41e2-ad86-\
2a942bebe077"]
}, Closed]]
}, Open  ]]
